    <!-- Narrative introduction (preserved from original) -->
    <div class="narrative">
      <p>At the end of a road crossing three kingdoms stands the World City, a metropolis so vast it has its own seasons. Thousands of craftspeople work in the same interconnected workshop: smiths, weavers, alchemists, scribes, all under the same titanic roof. The halls stretch for leagues, the archives fill entire floors, and yet everything is connected, everything is coherent.</p>
      <p>The City Architect greets you atop the central tower. From there, you can see the immensity of the workshop below.</p>
      <p>« Every village has its forge, its library, its temple. It is simple. It is autonomous. But when a thousand craftspeople must work together, share their tools, reuse their creations, <strong>a single giant workshop</strong> sometimes becomes more efficient than a thousand separate ones. That is the choice the greatest cities of the world have made. And it is a choice with a price. »</p>
      <p>The World City quest unfolds in <strong>two parts</strong>: first understand the strategic choice, then descend into the technical arcana.</p>
    </div>

